# Local Dev Workflow

## Two modes — know which one you need

### Mode 1: Daily development (default)
Use this for all feature work. Hot-reload, local Supabase, and seed scripts work.

```bash
pixi run db               # start local Supabase stack
pixi run dev              # backend + frontend together (from repo root)
```

- Backend: uvicorn with `--reload` on http://localhost:8000
- Frontend: Vite dev server on http://localhost:3000
- DB: Supabase local Postgres on localhost:54322
- `pixi run backend` auto-starts local Supabase if not running (via task dependency)
- Provision data (run once after first start):

```bash
pixi run provision -- --dev                 # org + departments + dev users
pixi run import -- --vendors --products    # real Hike POS data
```

### Mode 2: Production verification (before deploy)
Use this to confirm the Docker image builds and runs correctly against Postgres + Redis.

```bash
docker compose up --build    # nginx/certbot excluded via override profile
```

- Backend: http://localhost:8000 (Postgres, Redis connected)
- No hot-reload. Rebuild with `docker compose up --build` after code changes.
- `devtools/` scripts are intentionally excluded from the Docker image — run seeds in Mode 1.
- Docker build context is the workspace root: `docker build -f backend/Dockerfile .`

## Key ports
| Service  | Mode 1 (native) | Mode 2 (Docker) |
|----------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Backend  | :8000           | :8000           |
| Frontend | :3000           | —               |
| Postgres | :54322          | :5433           |

## Common dev commands

Install [Pixi](https://pixi.sh) once (`curl -fsSL https://pixi.sh/install.sh | sh`). All commands below run from the **project root** via `pixi run <task>` (`pixi task list` for discoverability).

```bash
pixi run test                    # all tests (backend then frontend)
pixi run test-backend -- -- …    # backend tests only (pytest; extra args after --)
pixi run test-frontend           # frontend tests only (vitest)
pixi run test-e2e -- -- …        # Playwright e2e (cwd e2e/)
pixi run lint-backend            # ruff lint Python
pixi run format-backend          # ruff format Python
pixi run lint-frontend           # ESLint frontend
pixi run format-frontend         # Prettier frontend
pixi run check                   # lint + format backend and frontend
pixi run commit                  # commitizen conventional commit
pixi run backend                 # backend only
pixi run frontend                # frontend only
pixi run provision -- -- …       # devtools provision
pixi run eval -- -- …           # LLM evals
pixi run db                      # start local Supabase stack
pixi run db-stop                 # stop local Supabase stack
pixi run db-reset                # reset local DB from migrations + seeds
pixi run clean                   # wipe backend venv + Python caches (see devtools/scripts/clean_repo.sh)
```

Never suggest `pip`, `python -m pytest`, or `ruff` directly. Python tooling runs through **`uv`** (`uv run` inside `pixi` tasks or directly at repo root). The project uses **uv workspaces** — the root `pyproject.toml` manages dev deps, `backend/pyproject.toml` has production deps only.

## Monorepo layout

```
sku-ops/
├── backend/          # deployable app + its tests
│   └── tests/        # backend unit/integration/api tests
├── frontend/         # React SPA (co-located unit tests in src/__tests__/)
├── e2e/              # cross-stack Playwright tests
├── devtools/         # seeds, evals, scripts — not deployed
├── pixi.toml         # task runner (dev, test, db, …)
└── pyproject.toml    # uv workspace root (dev deps, ruff, pytest, commitizen)
```

Each deployable owns its tests. Devtools live at the workspace root. The Docker image contains zero test or devtools code — `backend/tests/` is excluded via `.dockerignore`, devtools is structurally outside the `COPY backend/` layer, and `uv sync --no-dev` skips test deps.

## Frontend always proxies /api → localhost:8000
Configured in `frontend/vite.config.js`. Works with both modes as long as backend is on :8000.
